# Archive Documentation Maintenance

When adding new features or modifying existing features, check and update the Information Archive accordingly.

## What to Update

The Archive documentation lives in:
- `src/lib/archiveGuide/pageGuides.ts` — page-by-page `PAGE_GUIDES` entries
- `src/lib/archiveGuide/welcomeSections.ts` — welcome sections (rules, tips, DFP, etc.)
- `src/components/archive/ArchiveWelcome.tsx` — renders the welcome guide (icons in `PAGE_GUIDE_ICONS`)
- `public/archive-guide.html` — **printable offline guide** (auto-generated; do not edit by hand)

After updating archive content, run:

```bash
npm run generate-archive-guide
```

This regenerates `public/archive-guide.html` with working `#anchor` navigation, no site URLs, and content suitable for Save-as-PDF offline.

### When Adding a New Feature

1. Add an entry to `PAGE_GUIDES` in `src/lib/archiveGuide/pageGuides.ts` if the feature is user-facing
2. Add a matching icon in `PAGE_GUIDE_ICONS` inside `ArchiveWelcome.tsx`
3. Include: `id`, `title`, `description`, `details` array, and `relatesTo` array
4. Run `npm run generate-archive-guide`
3. Keep descriptions focused on **what members can do**, not technical implementation

### When Modifying Existing Features

1. Update the relevant `PAGE_GUIDES` entry if user-facing behavior changed
2. Update `details` bullet points to reflect new capabilities
3. Update `relatesTo` if the feature now integrates with other pages

## What NOT to Document

The Archive is for **regular members**. Do not include:

- Officer or super-admin-only features (dashboards, moderation tools)
- Backend implementation details
- Database schema or technical architecture
- Internal admin workflows or controls
- Debugging or developer information

## Example Entry

```tsx
{
  id: 'feature-name',
  title: 'Feature Name',
  icon: (
    <svg className="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
      <path strokeLinecap="round" strokeLinejoin="round" strokeWidth={1.5} d="..." />
    </svg>
  ),
  description: 'One-line description of what users can do.',
  details: [
    'First thing users can do with this feature',
    'Second capability or benefit',
    'Any requirements (e.g., verified RSI Handle)',
  ],
  relatesTo: ['Other Page', 'Related Feature'],
},
```

## Checklist

Before completing a feature implementation, verify:

- [ ] Is this feature visible to regular members?
- [ ] If yes, is there a `PAGE_GUIDES` entry for it?
- [ ] Does the entry accurately describe current behavior?
- [ ] Are related features listed in `relatesTo`?
- [ ] Did you run `npm run generate-archive-guide` so the printable HTML stays in sync?
